2. KEY DESIGN CHOICES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

A) TARGET-INFORMED SELECTION, NOT INSTRUCTION TRANSLATION
   Fe's capability/effect system prevents emitting EVM-specific ops
   when targeting WASM/native. The type system enforces this at
   compile time, not runtime checks. Storage access is a capability
   that EVM provides; linear memory is a different capability WASM
   provides. Generic code uses abstract capabilities.

B) WAFFLE FOR WASM (Bytecode Alliance, Ramsey's algorithm)
   Instead of hand-rolling a Stackifier for WASM control flow
   recovery, we target WAFFLE's SSA IR. WAFFLE handles:
   - Reducification (irreducible CFG → reducible)
   - Stackification (CFG → structured block/loop/if)
   - WASM emission
   Our job: faithful Sonatina IR → WAFFLE IR translation.
   Phi nodes → block params. Instructions → Operators.
   Sean recommended this approach.

C) NAGA FOR SPIR-V (Bytecode Alliance, gfx-rs)
   Instead of raw rspirv SPIR-V binary emission, we target Naga's
   expression DAG + statement tree IR. Naga handles:
   - SPIR-V validation and emission
   - Structured control flow via Statement::Loop/If
   - Optional WGSL output for debugging
   Key learning: Naga body/continuing blocks are sibling scopes —
   expressions emitted in body are NOT visible in continuing.
   Phi updates must go in body (end), not continuing.
   Expression scoping: Load/Binary/Unary need Emit statements;
   LocalVariable/Literal/GlobalVariable are always in scope.

D) ACTOR MODEL FOR CONTRACTS
   Fe's contract model is secretly an actor model:
   - recv arms = message handlers
   - init = constructor
   - synthetic runtime_root = mailbox dispatcher
   - effects = capabilities
   DispatchStrategy enum routes compilation:
   - EVM: calldata selector-based dispatch (synthetic root)
   - WASM: each recv arm → named export (no dispatcher)
   - Native: each recv arm → extern "C" symbol

E) HKT (type Foo<T> IN TRAITS) — Sub-PR 1 landed
   Parser accepts type Foo<T> in trait declarations.
   HIR stores generic_params on AssocTyDecl/AssocTyDef.
   Lowering collects generic params.
   Formatter, span, semantic view all updated.
   Kind system (Kind::Abs) already exists — just needs connection.
   Sub-PR 2 (kind computation + B::Ptr<u32> resolution) is next.
   Sub-PR 3 (impl conformance checking) follows.

F) UNIFIED COMPILATION ENTRY POINT
   unified.rs provides CompileTarget enum and compile_to_ir():
   - CompileTarget::Evm → standard EVM compilation
   - CompileTarget::Native/Wasm/Spirv → library mode with native ISA
   Same Sonatina IR module feeds all three non-EVM backends.

