3. ARCHITECTURE: SONATINA'S ROLE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Sonatina is the nimble, faithful translator between Fe and the
target backends. It does NOT reimpliment what WAFFLE/Naga provide:

  Fe → MIR → Sonatina IR (shared optimizations: SCCP, ADCE, LICM)
                ↓
  Backend trait: compile_module(&Module) → Artifact
                ↓
  ┌─────────────┼─────────────┐
  │             │             │
  Cranelift   WAFFLE        Naga
  (direct)    (SSA→SSA)     (SSA→DAG)

The Backend trait has one method: compile_module. Each backend owns
its internal pipeline. Cranelift translates instruction-by-instruction.
WAFFLE translates block-by-block with phi→blockparam conversion.
Naga translates to expression DAG with LocalVariable for phi state.

