5. KNOWN COMPROMISES / FOLLOW-UPS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

1. HKT Sub-PR 2+3: Kind computation + B::Ptr<u32> type resolution
   + impl conformance checking. Scoped but not implemented.

2. Overflow semantics differ: EVM wraps, native/WASM check (trap),
   SPIR-V has no overflow detection.

3. u256 only on Cranelift: WASM/SPIR-V limited to u64.
   u256 on WASM needs WAFFLE memory ops for limb storage.

4. Subtraction: Fe emits underflow checks that WAFFLE translator
   doesn't handle yet. Tests use add/mul to avoid this.

5. Storage not unified: EVM has SLOAD/SSTORE, others use
   InMemoryStorage. Needs Backend trait + HKTs.

6. objref params are value-passthrough on WASM: works for scalars
   but would break for compound types needing real pointer semantics.

