6. HKT DX RISK ANALYSIS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Fe already ships production HKTs (Abi::Decoder, Functor, Monad).
The Backend trait pushes HKT errors to contract developers who are
less type-theory-literate. Top 5 risks identified:

1. Unnormalized projections: "B::Word requires B: Backend" guidance
2. Kind mismatch: show "takes N type parameters" not "(* -> *)"
3. Effect/Backend interaction: detect EVM-specific effects in
   backend-generic code
4. Nested projection cascades: point at inner failing type
5. Fully-qualified display: show B::Ptr<u256> not <B as Backend>::Ptr

See fe-hkt-dx-risks.md for details with specific file paths.

